Re: Nenolod, the guy that wants to prove Bitcoin doesn't work.

Bitcointalk

2010-07-17 16:56:06 UTC - [11]Original Post

   0.3.2 has some security safeguards to lock in the block chain up to
   this point and limit the damage a little if someone gets 50%.
   But if someone has 50%+ of the CPU power and malicious intent, they can
   prove what it already says in the design document.
